text.section:
A generator of hazardous waste required by KRS Chapter 224 to register with the cabinet shall be subject to an annual registration fee by the cabinet and the fee shall be equal to the cost of review but shall not exceed the following amounts:
For one (1) to five (5) waste streams: three hundred dollars ($300);
For six (6) to ten (10) waste streams: three hundred fifty dollars ($350);
For eleven (11) to fifteen (15) waste streams: four hundred dollars ($400);
For sixteen (16) to twenty (20) waste streams: four hundred fifty dollars ($450);
For twenty-one (21) to twenty-five (25) waste streams: five hundred dollars ($500);
For twenty-six (26) to thirty (30) waste streams: five hundred fifty dollars ($550); and
For thirty-one (31) or more waste streams: six hundred dollars ($600).

If a generator of hazardous waste submits to the cabinet a registration to modify waste streams, the following fees shall be imposed:
For one (1) to five (5) waste streams: fifty dollars ($50);
For six (6) to ten (10) waste streams: one hundred dollars ($100);
For eleven (11) to fifteen (15) waste streams: one hundred fifty dollars ($150);
For sixteen (16) to twenty (20) waste streams: two hundred dollars ($200);
For twenty-one (21) to twenty-five (25) waste streams: two hundred fifty dollars ($250);
For twenty-six (26) to thirty (30) waste streams: three hundred dollars ($300); and
For thirty-one (31) or more waste streams: three hundred fifty dollars ($350).
